Babel: is a JavaScript compiler (transpiler) that converts modern syntax (ES6+) into older, widely-supported JavaScript (ES5) for browser compatibility

Webpack:  is a module bundler that packages all your project's files (JS, CSS, images) into optimized bundles for the browser

Loaders: allow webpack to process other types of files and convert them into valid modules that can be consumed by your application and added to the dependency graph

Functional Component: use functions

Class Component: use classes


- React Fragment - Usages:
    - React.Fragment
        function App() {
            return (
                <React.Fragment>
                    <h1>JStack's Blog</h1>
                    <h1>{category}</h1>
                </React.Fragment>
            )
        }

    - Fragment (Import)
        function App() {
            return (
                <Fragment>
                    <h1>JStack's Blog</h1>
                    <h1>{category}</h1>
                </Fragment>
            )
        }

    - <></>
        function App() {
            return (
                <>
                    <h1>JStack's Blog</h1>
                    <h1>{category}</h1>
                </>
            )
        }